_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟡 Minor_

**終了コードのチェックが欠如しています**

`git rev-parse HEAD`が失敗した場合（例：gitリポジトリ外で実行）、終了コードが非ゼロになりますが、現在の実装ではそれを検出せずに空文字列やゴミデータを返す可能性があります。


<details>
<summary>🐛 終了コードチェックの追加</summary>

```diff
 async function getCurrentHeadSha(): Promise<string> {
   const subprocess = Bun.spawn(["git", "rev-parse", "HEAD"], {
     stderr: "pipe",
     stdout: "pipe",
   });
   const stdout = await new Response(subprocess.stdout).text();
-  await subprocess.exited;
+  const exitCode = await subprocess.exited;
+  if (exitCode !== 0) {
+    throw new Error("Failed to get current HEAD SHA. Are you in a git repository?");
+  }
   return stdout.trim();
 }
```
</details>

<!-- suggestion_start -->

<details>
<summary>📝 Committable suggestion</summary>

> ‼️ **IMPORTANT**
> Carefully review the code before committing. Ensure that it accurately replaces the highlighted code, contains no missing lines, and has no issues with indentation. Thoroughly test & benchmark the code to ensure it meets the requirements.

```suggestion
async function getCurrentHeadSha(): Promise<string> {
  const subprocess = Bun.spawn(["git", "rev-parse", "HEAD"], {
    stderr: "pipe",
    stdout: "pipe",
  });
  const stdout = await new Response(subprocess.stdout).text();
  const exitCode = await subprocess.exited;
  if (exitCode !== 0) {
    throw new Error("Failed to get current HEAD SHA. Are you in a git repository?");
  }
  return stdout.trim();
}
```

</details>

<!-- suggestion_end -->

<details>
<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
Verify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.

In `@src/cli/commands/list.ts` around lines 109 - 117, getCurrentHeadSha currently
ignores the process exit status and may return garbage when "git rev-parse HEAD"
fails; after spawning via Bun.spawn and awaiting subprocess.exited, check the
subprocess exit code/status (e.g., subprocess.status or exitCode) and if
non-zero read subprocess.stderr (or the error text) and throw or return a clear
error/empty result including that stderr message; update getCurrentHeadSha to
perform this check and surface the stderr when subprocess indicates failure.
```

</details>

