**複数の Git 呼び出しで終了コード未検査のまま処理継続しています**

Line 10、Line 61〜Line 65 のいずれかが失敗しても exit code をチェックせず後段に進行するため、誤った状態を前提に進行します。同ファイル内の他の Git 呼び出し（Line 12, 21, 32, 52, 74 等）では `{ exitCode, stderr }` を適切に分解して検査しているため、ここも統一的に exit code を検査する必要があります。

特に git add 失敗は commit 失敗につながり、git fetch/worktree add 失敗は不正な worktree path を返却してしまいます。

<details>
<summary>修正案</summary>

```diff
-  await runGit(["add", "--all"], { workingDirectory: worktreePath });
+  const { exitCode: addExitCode, stderr: addStderr } = await runGit(["add", "--all"], {
+    workingDirectory: worktreePath,
+  });
+  if (addExitCode !== 0) {
+    throw new Error(`git add failed (exit ${String(addExitCode)}): ${addStderr}`);
+  }

   if (stdout.trim()) {
-    await runGit(["fetch", "origin", `${branchName}:${branchName}`]);
-    await runGit(["worktree", "add", worktreePath, branchName]);
+    const { exitCode: fetchExitCode, stderr: fetchStderr } = await runGit([
+      "fetch",
+      "origin",
+      `${branchName}:${branchName}`,
+    ]);
+    if (fetchExitCode !== 0) {
+      throw new Error(`git fetch failed (exit ${String(fetchExitCode)}): ${fetchStderr}`);
+    }
+    const { exitCode: addWorktreeExitCode, stderr: addWorktreeStderr } = await runGit([
+      "worktree",
+      "add",
+      worktreePath,
+      branchName,
+    ]);
+    if (addWorktreeExitCode !== 0) {
+      throw new Error(`git worktree add failed (exit ${String(addWorktreeExitCode)}): ${addWorktreeStderr}`);
+    }
   } else {
-    await runGit(["worktree", "add", "--orphan", "-b", branchName, worktreePath]);
+    const { exitCode: orphanExitCode, stderr: orphanStderr } = await runGit([
+      "worktree",
+      "add",
+      "--orphan",
+      "-b",
+      branchName,
+      worktreePath,
+    ]);
+    if (orphanExitCode !== 0) {
+      throw new Error(`git worktree add --orphan failed (exit ${String(orphanExitCode)}): ${orphanStderr}`);
+    }
   }
```
</details>

<details>
<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
Verify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.

In `@src/actions/branch.ts` around lines 10 - 11, The git add invocation using
runGit(["add", "--all"], { workingDirectory: worktreePath }) does not check the
exit code; update it to destructure the result (e.g., const { exitCode, stderr }
= await runGit(...)) and handle non-zero exit codes the same way as other calls
in this file (log or throw using stderr) so failures (git add, fetch, worktree
add) do not allow the function to continue on an invalid state; reference runGit
and worktreePath when making the change and mirror the existing error-check
pattern used for other runGit calls in this module.
```

</details>

